SIMPLE: defervescency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defervescency
<hw>De`fer*ves"cency</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>defervescere</ets> to
grow cool.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A subsiding from a state of
ebullition; loss of heat; lukewarmness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>defervescency</qex> in holy actions.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The subsidence of a febrile
process; <as>as, the stage of <ex>defervescence</ex> in
pneumonia</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defeudalize</ent>⟦br⟧
